The Chronicle The day will start with a short story writing workshop facilitated by Mgcini Nyoni at the National Art Gallery from 10AM to 4PM. It will coincide with the Arts and Culture Teachers’ Platform that will be convened by Dr Sibanda and Jasen Mphepo at Eveline High School. In the evening, Sunduza Dance Company will showcase the Adventure of Robert Moffat at Bulawayo Theatre from 6PM to 7PM followed by Little Theatre productions’ The Storm from 7.30PM. Comedians, King Kandoro, MaForty, Andrew Manyika, Tlanda and Ezra will wrap up the day with a comedy show dubbed Borderline Insanity at Hope Centre from 6PM to 8PM.